UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2598
1 A RESOLUTION recognizing the Nehemiah Alliance National 52-Day Rebuild
2 Initiative and encouraging voluntary prayer, fasting, and reflection.
3 WHEREAS, the Nehemiah Alliance has launched a historic National 52-Day
4 Rebuild Initiative, calling the people of the United States to unified prayer, fasting, and
5 repentance for the purpose of rebuilding the spiritual walls of blessing and protection
6 around our 50 states and nation; and
7 WHEREAS, the visionaries and leaders behind the Nehemiah Alliance were shaped
8 by Kentucky roots, born and raised as citizens of this historic Commonwealth, and
9 Kentucky is honored to be connected to this now-national initiative; and
10 WHEREAS, from its founding, the United States of America has been shaped by
11 enduring Judeo-Christian principles of faith, liberty, and justice, and has long understood
12 itself to be one nation under God. Throughout our history, Americans have turned to
13 these principles in challenging moments to seek renewal, unity, and moral clarity; and
14 WHEREAS, the Nehemiah Alliance draws inspiration from the biblical account of
15 Nehemiah, who—through the favor of Heaven, the authorization of government, and the
16 cooperation of leaders—rebuilt the broken walls of Jerusalem in 52 days; and in that
17 same spirit, during America’s 250th anniversary, this 52-Day Initiative calls Americans
18 to recognize that the moral, cultural, and spiritual foundations of our society require our
19 attention and action; and
20 WHEREAS, Kentucky holds a unique historical precedent through one of its native
21 sons, President Abraham Lincoln, who, during one of the most divided seasons in our
22 Nation’s history, issued Proclamation 97—appointing a day of National Humiliation,
23 Fasting, and Prayer in 1863, calling Americans to humble themselves, repent, and seek
24 divine guidance for the healing of the land; and
25 WHEREAS, beginning at sundown on September 10, 2026, and concluding at
26 sundown on All Saints’ Sunday, November 1, 2026, this Initiative invites people across
27 our nation to humble themselves before Almighty God through prayer, repentance, and
Page 1 of 3
