UNOFFICIAL COPY 26 RS BR 2598
1 periods of fasting as each person is individually led; and
2 WHEREAS, the purpose of this Initiative is to rebuild our walls, restore our homes,
3 revive our hearts, and renew liberty and justice for all, reunifying us as one nation under
4 God; and
5 WHEREAS, the mission of the Nehemiah Alliance is grounded in the call of
6 scripture, including the promise recorded in 2 Chronicles 7:14, that as His people pray,
7 call upon His name, and repent of their sins and those of our nation, God will hear from
8 Heaven and heal our land; and the Alliance seeks to reflect the Body of Christ by
9 bringing together leaders, pastors, organizations, and intercessors across denominations,
10 ethnicities, and spheres of influence; and
11 WHEREAS, in accordance with 1 Timothy 2:1–2, participants are encouraged to
12 serve as modern-day gatekeepers, building a spiritual wall around their homes and
13 interceding for their families, neighborhoods, schools, churches, businesses, and all
14 leaders in authority; and
15 WHEREAS, drawing from historical precedent, including General George S.
16 Patton’s commissioning of a common prayer for all his troops preceding victory in World
17 War II, participants will unite in one voice throughout the Initiative to intercede using a
18 United Prayer for America; and
19 WHEREAS, during the 52 days, focused prayers will be made for spheres of
20 culture; the 50 states and territories, the nation’s capital, Congress, Supreme Court, the
21 President and his Administration, and upcoming national elections; and
22 WHEREAS, on Saturday, October 31, 2026, and All Saints’ Sunday, November 1,
23 2026, people of faith from across the nation will gather online and in person—including
24 on the National Mall, in Washington, D.C.—in sacred assembly to pray, fast, repent, and
25 stand;
26 NOW, THEREFORE,
27 Be it resolved by the Senate of the General Assembly of the Commonwealth of
Page 2 of 3
